<item>
            <title>[LU-12039] Fix &apos;lfs mkdir&apos; in sanity-selinux</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12039</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity-selinux test_2b and test_20c assume that directory created with &apos;lfs mkdir&apos; will be on MDT0, but it is not necessarily the case because they forget to use the &apos;-i 0&apos; flag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push a patch to address this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
